\f2\fs18\fsmilli9333 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 
\f3\b\fs24 A review of dozen of zebra crossings in Berlin showed that pressing the "Please touch" button at almost all zebra crossings makes no difference to how early the traffic light changes. With the new Berlin Pedestrian Protection Act, have new devices been ordered to solve this problem?
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li944\sl280\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0 \cf2 \strokec2 Your thesis that the
\f1 \cf3 \strokec3  
\f0 \cf2 \strokec2 switches are fundamentally defective, with a probability bordering on certainty, does not apply.
\f1 \cf3 \strokec3  
\f0 \cf2 \strokec2 Pressing the button detects the pedestrian's wish to cross and, depending on the situation \ul ,\ulnone  triggers \ul different\ulnone  reactions in the switching program of the traffic light system.
\f1 \cf3 \strokec3  
\f0 \cf2 \strokec2 Namely this optionally:
\f1 \cf3 \strokec3  \
\pard\pardeftab720\li1904\sl360\sa0\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs32 \cf2 \strokec2 1. A green phase is requested if the system does not provide for a fixed green phase anyway.
\f1\fs24 \cf3 \strokec3  \

\f0\fs32 \cf2 \strokec2 2. At certain traffic lights (especially those with visually impaired buttons) an extended green time is requested in order to be able to cross the entire street (more comfortably).
\f1\fs24 \cf3 \strokec3  \

\f0\fs32 \cf2 \strokec2 3. Acoustic and tactile signals are requested (at the same time) for people with visual impairments or for the blind.
\f1\fs24 \cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li944\sl280\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0 \cf2 \strokec2 The functionality of the buttons is therefore \ul not always\ulnone  simply that green for pedestrians comes immediately after the push of a button (there are also such circuits if the local circumstances suggest this is the best solution).
\f1 \cf3 \strokec3 \

\f0 \cf2 \strokec2 Of course, there may also be defective or temporarily out of service switches on traffic lights in individual cases. It is not plausible that this should be the case \'93at dozens of\'94 traffic lights, as you write.
\f1 \cf3 \strokec3  \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\sa240\partightenfactor0

