\f2\fs18\fsmilli9333 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 
\f3\b\fs24 What other steps are being taken under the new Pedestrian Act to make life better for pedestrians?
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li944\sl280\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0 \cf2 \strokec2 The state of Berlin was the first federal state in Germany to \ul legally\ulnone  enshrine the promotion of pedestrian traffic - in the Mobility Act. This creates a clear commitment that goes beyond mere plans, declarations of intent and official traffic strategies. Walking should become more attractive - among other things through these measures:
\f1 \cf3 \strokec3  \
\pard\pardeftab720\li1424\sl280\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf3 \'e8
\f2\fs18\fsmilli9333  
\f0\fs32 \cf2 \strokec2 Berlin wants to create more spaces in which car traffic plays no or only a subordinate role, such as pedestrian zones, traffic-calmed streets or play streets.
\f1\fs24 \cf3 \strokec3  \

\f4 \'e8
\f2\fs18\fsmilli9333  
\f0\fs32 \cf2 \strokec2 In the future, footpaths will be better lit, especially in less busy areas of the city, so that people feel safer.
\f1\fs24 \cf3 \strokec3  \

\f4 \'e8
\f2\fs18\fsmilli9333  
\f0\fs32 \cf2 \strokec2 In order to make it easier to cross roads and to increase safety, more central islands are to be built, more curbs are to be lowered and sidewalks are to be expanded.
\f1\fs24 \cf3 \strokec3  \

\f4 \'e8
\f2\fs18\fsmilli9333  
\f0\fs32 \cf2 \strokec2 In the case of wide streets, the green phases for pedestrians should be so long in future that there is no need to wait on the central island. In the case of so-called blind traffic lights, the existing option is also being expanded to extend the green phase at the push of a button.
\f1\fs24 \cf3 \strokec3  \

\f4 \'e8
\f2\fs18\fsmilli9333  
\f0\fs32 \cf2 \strokec2 Routes to school are to be made safer - among other things through more school guides as well as construction and traffic measures in the vicinity of schools.
\f1\fs24 \cf3 \strokec3  \

\f4 \'e8
\f2\fs18\fsmilli9333  
\f0\fs32 \cf2 \strokec2 Senate and districts are increasing their staff to plan for foot traffic. Similar to bicycle traffic, there should be two pedestrian traffic points per district, plus additional points in the Senate Administration.
\f1\fs24 \cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li944\sl280\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0 \cf2 \strokec2 At the end of January 2021, the members of the Berlin state parliament decided to expand the mobility law to include \ul pedestrian traffic\ulnone  . Accessibility, reducing the number of accidents and increasing user satisfaction are important goals that Berlin wants to achieve with the law.
